        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Line 20: `let sessionIndexerLagDetected = false;` \u2014 set to true at line 361 when indexer check fails. Never set back to false. Every subsequent publishPost call will emit the warning at line 268 even if the indexer recovered. In a long-lived process (event-runner), this means a single transient lag permanently marks all future publishes."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either reset to false when a publish IS confirmed in the indexer, or scope the flag to a session/call context instead of module level",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "feff6248"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-28T17:34:30+00:00",
